<item>
            <title>[LU-2878] &quot;make install&quot; Broken</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2878</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;A recent set of Livermore changes to the build system has broken &quot;make install&quot;.  &quot;make all&quot; still works.  For some reason, ldiskfs is failing a dependency check:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt; *** Missing ldiskfs symbols. Ensure you have built ldiskfs:
 *** - /home/build/lustre-release/ldiskfs/ldiskfs/Module.symvers
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Either a- this needs to be fixed so developers who don&apos;t want to have to build RPM&apos;s every time can continue to use &quot;make install&quot;, or b- &quot;make install&quot; should be removed.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="17717">LU-2878</key>
            <summary>&quot;make install&quot; Broken</summary>
